1
00:00:01,080 --> 00:00:03,280
ALL DEPICTED EVENTS ARE FICTIONAL

2
00:00:17,040 --> 00:00:19,000
<i>A shark washes ashore</i>

3
00:00:19,080 --> 00:00:21,400
I forgot.
I won't get to see Qin during break.

4
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:24,920
Qin, please practice
with him during the break.

5
00:00:28,360 --> 00:00:30,800
- And you're here by yourself?
- Do you see anybody else?

6
00:00:33,320 --> 00:00:34,440
<i>I need some advice.</i>

7
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:36,160
<i>I'm serious about my singing.</i>

8
00:00:36,240 --> 00:00:38,320
I can't sing, and I don't know what to do.

9
00:00:38,920 --> 00:00:40,480
<i>I don't want to burden you.</i>

10
00:00:40,560 --> 00:00:42,400
Do you want to
practice singing at my place?

11
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:47,000
You invited me to your place?

12
00:01:01,080 --> 00:01:02,080
What are you looking at?

13
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:05,400
I've never been here.

14
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:09,320
It's nothing special.

15
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:14,480
Your room smells nice.

16
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:17,200
And yours is disgusting.

17
00:01:19,120 --> 00:01:21,600
Don't make assumptions
if you haven't been to my place.

18
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:30,960
You even got a teddy. It's so adorable!

19
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:32,600
From an old fling.

20
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:43,520
And you kept it? You still have feelings.

21
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:47,440
An old fling. We parted ways ages ago.

22
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:50,320
The teddy did nothing wrong.
Why should I throw it away?

23
00:01:53,720 --> 00:01:55,440
That cuts deep.

24
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:11,360
Something like that.

25
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,120
How did I do?

26
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:15,000
You did fine.

27
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:16,680
Was it out of tune?

28
00:04:18,160 --> 00:04:19,160
Not really.

29
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:25,120
Do you have a prize for me?

30
00:04:31,040 --> 00:04:32,440
You're crossing the line.

31
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,800
Let's call it a day. It's getting late.

32
00:05:34,360 --> 00:05:35,280
Thank you.

33
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:55,640
Back to your house.

34
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,080
I live in a condo, not a house.

35
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:01,640
Whatever. Go to your condo already.

36
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,800
It's my older brother's, not mine.

37
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:05,480
His name is Funan.

38
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:07,480
He's not as cute as me.
But he lives at home.

39
00:06:07,560 --> 00:06:08,760
Did I ask?

40
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:11,160
Just leave. I don't care.

41
00:06:11,240 --> 00:06:15,360
Both my house and condo
are so far from here.

42
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:19,920
Would it be okay
if I spent the night here?

43
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:20,840
No.

44
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:25,840
Without hesitation? I understand.

45
00:06:26,400 --> 00:06:28,800
Being here is beyond my wildest dreams.

46
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:34,960
Actually, you're worried
I'll do nasty things to you, right?

47
00:06:40,680 --> 00:06:42,000
So dramatic.

48
00:06:45,680 --> 00:06:47,200
Hey, let me see it.

49
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:49,520
Hey.

50
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:56,680
You're worried about me.

51
00:06:58,120 --> 00:06:59,000
I'm counting to ten.

52
00:06:59,080 --> 00:07:01,680
Get out of my room,
or I won't let you back in.

53
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:04,080
Ten.

54
00:07:04,760 --> 00:07:05,680
Nine.

55
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:08,160
Eight. Seven.

56
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:10,160
Six.

57
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:12,600
Five.

58
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,480
Do you want me to send you flying out?

59
00:07:18,440 --> 00:07:19,920
I'll get to stay longer, right?

60
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:24,120
A perfect dodge.

61
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,280
Okay! I'll leave now!

62
00:07:27,360 --> 00:07:29,240
Next time, let me stay over.

63
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:39,880
I wasn't finished.
I made you blush, didn't I?

64
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,240
Mom?

65
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:02,760
Hello, Mom?

66
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:04,080
<i>Hello, Duang.</i>

67
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:07,120
You called me. You miss me, don't you?

68
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:09,320
<i>Of course, I do!</i>

69
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:12,840
<i>You're on your semester break, right?</i>
<i>Come home and see me?</i>

70
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:18,680
I'm actually thinking of coming home.
I really miss you, Mom.

71
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:20,360
<i>What? Really?</i>

72
00:08:20,440 --> 00:08:22,800
<i>How about coming home right now?</i>

73
00:08:22,880 --> 00:08:24,640
<i>I'll make your favorite soup.</i>

74
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,880
I'd better get going then.

75
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:29,000
I'll be there in a flash.

76
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,440
Why are you smiling?

77
00:08:59,520 --> 00:09:02,200
You didn't get up when I woke you up
for our workout.

78
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:05,400
Now that you're home,
won't you workout with me?

79
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:08,120
Look at Funan, he came.

80
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:12,120
You'd better take care of
your health, all right?

81
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,360
That's right.

82
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:16,160
It was too early.

83
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:20,120
I just wanted to sleep in,
now that I'm home, Dad.

84
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:23,960
What's on your phone?
Why were you smiling?

85
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,120
Let me see it.

86
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,480
Nope. It was nothing.

87
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:30,880
I was doomscrolling.

88
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:33,680
That's not a good way to spend your time.

89
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:38,160
You've always been like this.
You're being too laid-back, Duang.

90
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:47,160
Why not stay home for your break?

91
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,960
I told Mom I have an event at university.

92
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,360
An event? What is it?

93
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:53,600
Why does it have to take place
during the break?

94
00:09:54,840 --> 00:09:57,960
I asked Mom, and she told me to ask you.

95
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:01,120
Are you hiding something from u?

96
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:03,640
Or have you been doing
something pointless?

97
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,960
Nope. I wasn't lying.

98
00:10:06,040 --> 00:10:07,440
It's not anything pointless either.

99
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:09,440
I'm actually working
on a university project.

100
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:11,360
My seniors needed my help.

101
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,680
Can you really trust the seniors?

102
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:16,120
He's right. Can you trust them?

103
00:10:16,600 --> 00:10:19,800
You shouldn't listen
to what they say too much.

104
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:25,400
I know! I'm a grown-up now.

105
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:28,880
I know my way around things.

106
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:31,080
Come here, you.

107
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:33,640
You know, yet you're so forgetful.

108
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:36,320
Last month,
you forgot to pay the electricity bill.

109
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:41,520
What would you do
if it weren't for your brother?

110
00:10:47,160 --> 00:10:48,840
I'm a lost cause.

111
00:10:56,920 --> 00:10:57,760
Mom!

112
00:10:57,840 --> 00:11:00,200
- I have something to tell you!
- Duang!

113
00:11:00,280 --> 00:11:02,560
What are you cooking?
It smells delightful!

114
00:11:02,640 --> 00:11:04,160
Dad, I'm going to take a shower.

115
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:05,560
Hey, Funan!

116
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:07,920
Mom!

117
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,240
What is it, Duang?

118
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,800
Dad and Funan are picking on me.

119
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:15,720
What? Why the outburst?
They always tease you, no?

120
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:23,040
Who made all of this? It looks so tasty.

121
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:26,840
You said that you wanted
Betong chicken and spicy salad.

122
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:29,200
- So I made it all just for you.
- You're right.

123
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,360
I love you so much, Mom.

124
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:33,120
Eat up and enjoy, Duang.

125
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,200
Qin?

126
00:11:41,360 --> 00:11:43,320
- Are you back from the condo?
- Hello, son.

127
00:11:43,400 --> 00:11:46,320
Here. Have some fruit.

128
00:11:49,680 --> 00:11:51,120
Here you go, son.

129
00:11:52,720 --> 00:11:53,680
Thank you.

130
00:11:53,760 --> 00:11:56,480
- Here's yours, honey.
- Thank you, sweetie.

131
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,920
<i>This is Betong chicken.</i>

132
00:12:11,000 --> 00:12:14,160
<i>Although it doesn't look lovely,</i>
<i>it sure is tasty,</i>

133
00:12:14,720 --> 00:12:16,200
<i>just like me.</i>

134
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:20,480
<i>Then there's spicy salad with salted egg,</i>
<i>my favorite.</i>

135
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:23,440
<i>I'm about to have breakfast.</i>

136
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:25,720
<i>I wish you were here with me.</i>

137
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,440
Glued to your phone, I see.

138
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:37,280
Are you glued to the phone
or someone you're talking to?

139
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:39,000
I want to know who it is now.

140
00:12:40,040 --> 00:12:43,320
I'd introduce the person to you,
but I'm not sure if they'll say yes.

141
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:46,360
What? Are you taking this one seriously?

142
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:48,280
As seriously as I'll ever be, Mom!

143
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:53,280
Duang. You scared me.

144
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,760
PODDUANG
HAVE YOU EATEN?

145
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:56,920
Qin.

146
00:12:58,920 --> 00:13:01,200
Finish the fruit first
before looking at your phone.

147
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,920
Yes.

148
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,960
Was it a friend from university?

149
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:11,440
Yes.

150
00:13:11,520 --> 00:13:13,880
Have you made a lot of friends there?

151
00:13:14,440 --> 00:13:17,400
You should invite some over.
We can cook for them.

152
00:13:17,480 --> 00:13:19,520
- Not many.
- That's okay, son.

153
00:13:19,600 --> 00:13:21,040
But choose your friends carefully.

154
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:23,960
For the sake of your future,

155
00:13:24,040 --> 00:13:26,960
having good connections

156
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:28,520
goes a long way.

157
00:13:30,280 --> 00:13:31,160
Yes.

158
00:13:41,680 --> 00:13:42,920
<i>Of course I have.</i>

159
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:47,120
<i>I'd have starved</i>
<i>if I'd waited for you to ask.</i>

160
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:49,480
Qin.

161
00:13:55,640 --> 00:13:56,640
I'm sorry.

162
00:13:57,840 --> 00:14:00,320
Sweetie, it's okay. He's probably done.

163
00:14:04,920 --> 00:14:08,840
Qin, we're heading out.
Would you like to join us?

164
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,520
I'll stay. Go ahead.

165
00:14:12,600 --> 00:14:15,160
You're not going to ask
where we're off to?

166
00:14:17,360 --> 00:14:19,080
Where are you off to?

167
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,440
To our office, of course.

168
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:24,840
Qin, it's probably about time.

169
00:14:25,400 --> 00:14:27,760
You should come with us
when you have the chance.

170
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:30,880
Maybe later. I have rehearsal.

171
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:36,120
You do realize what we're doing
is for your future, right?

172
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,640
I know you're into fragrances.

173
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:38,880
Yes.

174
00:14:39,680 --> 00:14:42,440
I've seen you working in
the fragrance industry since I was little.

175
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:45,000
Of course I'm passionate about it.

176
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:47,480
Duang.

177
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,880
Living alone,
do you manage to eat properly?

178
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:54,680
I skip meals when I get lazy or forget.

179
00:14:54,760 --> 00:14:58,080
But I keep Funan's room clean.
You can see for yourself.

180
00:14:58,160 --> 00:14:59,880
I believe you, Duang.

181
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:02,320
If you need anything,
you have to tell me, okay?

182
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:06,240
You'll be the first to know, I promise.
Pinky promise.

183
00:15:09,520 --> 00:15:10,600
- Promise.
- Promise.

184
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:13,040
Promise. Promise.

185
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:14,160
Promise.

186
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,520
- Promise.
- Promise.

187
00:15:19,920 --> 00:15:22,840
By the way, on Instagram,

188
00:15:22,920 --> 00:15:25,520
your friend tagged you.
You've been singing?

189
00:15:26,560 --> 00:15:28,360
The seniors needed my help.

190
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:32,160
Hey, Mom showed me the video.

191
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,680
You have a natural gift for singing.

192
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,880
You should've studied voice.

193
00:15:38,760 --> 00:15:40,920
Jazz suits me better.

194
00:15:43,400 --> 00:15:45,840
Okay, that's fine.

195
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:47,960
When you're close to graduating,

196
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:51,040
I'll have you train
at my friend's record label.

197
00:15:55,080 --> 00:15:59,360
Sweetie, I think it's too soon.
Qin is just a freshman.

198
00:15:59,440 --> 00:16:02,440
We should let him choose
what he wants to study.

199
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:07,160
I just want to
pave the way for his career.

200
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:14,440
<i>What are you having, Qin?</i>

201
00:16:15,000 --> 00:16:17,040
<i>Do you know what I want to enjoy?</i>

202
00:16:24,920 --> 00:16:26,720
<i>I want to enjoy a meal with you.</i>

203
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:34,200
<i>Anyone but you.</i>

204
00:16:36,160 --> 00:16:37,800
- Ouch!
- Duang?

205
00:16:39,680 --> 00:16:41,880
- Duang!
- My chest hurts!

206
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,960
What's wrong? Where does it hurt?

207
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:45,760
That's your heart!

208
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:47,840
- Honey! Duang is in pain!
- Duang!

209
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:49,440
He can't breathe!

210
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:51,320
I told you to take care of your health.

211
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:53,000
- It hurts here.
- Told you!

212
00:16:53,080 --> 00:16:54,400
- Here.
- I told you so.

213
00:16:54,480 --> 00:16:56,320
- Use me as an example.
- He fell.

214
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:59,360
- Duang fell.
- Does it hurt that bad, son?

215
00:16:59,440 --> 00:17:00,640
It's that bad.

216
00:17:00,720 --> 00:17:02,160
- Let's get him to a hospital.
- Yes?

217
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,720
- Which hospital?
- Get the phone!

218
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:04,920
He has insurance.

219
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,400
Yeah.

220
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:16,240
<i>I'm upset. I haven't been home in ages.</i>

221
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:17,560
<i>The moment I saw my dad,</i>

222
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:19,319
he turned into a grumbling machine,

223
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:21,040
complaining I hadn't been exercising

224
00:17:21,119 --> 00:17:23,400
and asking why I'm staying home for break.

225
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:26,920
<i>When I told him about the event,</i>
<i>he told me I was being nonsensical.</i>

226
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:27,960
<i>Funan too.</i>

227
00:17:28,040 --> 00:17:30,280
Complaining that
I forgot to pay the electricity bill.

228
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:32,080
Making me feel like I'm always wrong.

229
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:36,040
Don't beat yourself up.
They're worried about you.

230
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:38,440
They're treating me like I'm a baby boy.

231
00:17:38,520 --> 00:17:40,400
<i>I'm not a kid anymore, am I?</i>

232
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:41,760
You're the youngest son.

233
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:42,800
No matter what,

234
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:45,320
your mom will always see you as her baby.

235
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:48,600
What would you know, American boy?

236
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:50,640
<i>No use in rambling.</i>

237
00:17:50,720 --> 00:17:53,040
<i>I wish they'd let me fly</i>
<i>on my own like you.</i>

238
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:55,320
It's okay.

239
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,400
<i>Don't be upset.</i>

240
00:17:58,600 --> 00:18:00,880
Let's change the subject. I want to brag.

241
00:18:01,680 --> 00:18:03,320
- About Qin?
- It's Qin.

242
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:06,560
What? You knew?

243
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:09,280
I didn't even have to guess. That's it.

244
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:11,080
<i>Wait, I didn't even get to talk about it!</i>

245
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,640
<i>Jamie, are you listening to me?</i>

246
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:38,880
I don't wanna hear it, Duang.
That's it. I'm having a drink.

247
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:14,680
<i>What are you doing?</i>

248
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:15,960
<i>Have you gone to bed?</i>

249
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:25,200
WANNA MEET UP TOMORROW?

250
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:29,080
EVERYONE IS COMING

251
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,240
CALLING

252
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:44,640
You called me?

253
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,320
It was an accident.

254
00:19:47,040 --> 00:19:51,400
Right, an accident.
Just tell me if you miss me.

255
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:54,960
You should get your brain checked.

256
00:19:55,520 --> 00:19:58,080
You're making me blush.

257
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,160
All I have in my brain is you.

258
00:20:01,480 --> 00:20:04,000
<i>What did you do today?</i>

259
00:20:04,560 --> 00:20:05,800
<i>I stayed at home.</i>

260
00:20:05,880 --> 00:20:08,080
I stayed at home, too!

261
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:11,120
But Funan is so annoying.

262
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:14,040
- Your older brother?
<i>- You remember?</i>

263
00:20:14,640 --> 00:20:15,800
He has a weird name.

264
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:17,480
<i>My parents are archaeologists.</i>

265
00:20:17,560 --> 00:20:19,320
That's why they named us after old coins.

266
00:20:19,400 --> 00:20:20,720
Funan.

267
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:24,040
Duang, short for Podduang.

268
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:28,200
<i>Your name is also weird.</i>
<i>I've never heard it before.</i>

269
00:20:28,280 --> 00:20:29,840
It's Qin. How is it strange?

270
00:20:30,400 --> 00:20:31,640
Does it mean something?

271
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:34,320
<i>The meaning is twofold.</i>

272
00:20:34,400 --> 00:20:37,720
It either means "to criticize"
or "beauty."

273
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:38,880
<i>Yours is the latter.</i>

274
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:40,520
Your name means "beauty."

275
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:43,880
<i>Glass half full, or glass half empty.</i>

276
00:20:43,960 --> 00:20:47,200
My mom says it's natural
to have good and bad sides.

277
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:52,400
Sounds sophisticated and extraordinary.

278
00:20:57,720 --> 00:20:59,720
You called me
to say "sweet dreams," right?

279
00:20:59,800 --> 00:21:01,880
I know what you're trying to do.

280
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,080
Suit yourself.

281
00:21:03,160 --> 00:21:05,880
I miss you to death, you know?

282
00:21:07,720 --> 00:21:09,120
- I'm hanging up.
<i>- Wait.</i>

283
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:13,200
Okay, see you tomorrow, babe. Good night.

284
00:21:17,640 --> 00:21:20,200
Come on. I wasn't done talking!

285
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:09,440
Don't forget to dream of me

286
00:22:09,520 --> 00:22:11,520
so that you'll have good dreams.

287
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:29,200
<i>"To criticize" and "beauty."</i>

288
00:22:29,280 --> 00:22:30,680
I like both meanings.

289
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,360
What? You're leaving already?

290
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:54,920
Got a hot date with a girl?

291
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:58,960
- A little bird told me that.
- You're partially right.

292
00:22:59,520 --> 00:23:01,120
But I'm not a girl.

293
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:02,080
Seriously?

294
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:06,400
My heart longs for this person.
Gender isn't my concern.

295
00:23:09,120 --> 00:23:11,000
Don't forget to introduce them to me.

296
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:13,800
Just you wait.

297
00:23:24,440 --> 00:23:26,360
- Duang.
- Yes?

298
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:27,680
Where are you off to?

299
00:23:28,160 --> 00:23:29,240
To dance practice.

300
00:23:30,120 --> 00:23:31,720
- Dance practice.
- Wait.

301
00:23:32,280 --> 00:23:33,240
What dance?

302
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:36,160
It's for the event I told you about.

303
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:40,760
My professor knows about it too.

304
00:23:40,840 --> 00:23:42,360
I'm not doing anything bad.

305
00:23:42,920 --> 00:23:45,960
Moreover, I made a promise
to do my very best.

306
00:23:46,040 --> 00:23:47,600
So I have to practice a lot.

307
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:53,080
In that case,
I'll have Funan drive you there.

308
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:55,800
- Funan, drive him to--
- Dad, no need.

309
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:57,640
I can drive.

310
00:23:58,640 --> 00:24:01,600
Also, you're sending Funan
to keep tabs on me, aren't you?

311
00:24:02,520 --> 00:24:04,640
It's just an ordinary event.

312
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:06,400
I'll send you pictures later.

313
00:24:07,120 --> 00:24:09,840
Duang, when you do something,

314
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,040
be passionate and serious about it.

315
00:24:12,120 --> 00:24:13,640
Don't slack off too much, okay?

316
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,840
Yes, I know that, Dad.

317
00:24:16,320 --> 00:24:19,160
I know I need to keep my word.

318
00:24:19,240 --> 00:24:21,240
If I don't,

319
00:24:21,320 --> 00:24:24,800
I'll seem unreliable and incompetent.

320
00:24:27,520 --> 00:24:28,680
I'm worried about you.

321
00:24:29,880 --> 00:24:30,760
Right.

322
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:33,840
- I'll be going now. Bye-bye.
- Get going, son.

323
00:24:38,320 --> 00:24:40,760
- Drive safely.
- Thank you.

324
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,920
You called me, Dad?

325
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:49,360
Come.

326
00:24:50,440 --> 00:24:52,240
I want you to talk to your brother

327
00:24:53,040 --> 00:24:55,920
and warn him not to slack off too much.

328
00:24:56,000 --> 00:24:57,760
I thought it'd be something else.

329
00:24:57,840 --> 00:25:00,800
I've been telling him that.

330
00:25:00,880 --> 00:25:03,520
He's gotten a lot better lately.

331
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:06,720
He's still young. Keep an eye on him.

332
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:11,000
He said that the event he's working on
involves dancing.

333
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:14,200
All right, Dad.

334
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:17,840
I slowed down the music.

335
00:25:18,440 --> 00:25:20,360
The seniors helped with the choreography

336
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:22,000
to match the slower tempo.

337
00:25:22,080 --> 00:25:23,000
Let's give it a go.

338
00:25:24,200 --> 00:25:26,600
One, two, three,

339
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,720
- Three…
- Four.

340
00:25:31,120 --> 00:25:32,040
One more time.

341
00:25:33,280 --> 00:25:34,960
Your hands go like this, an L shape.

342
00:25:35,040 --> 00:25:36,720
Three and four.

343
00:25:37,280 --> 00:25:38,280
My arms are killing me.

344
00:25:39,480 --> 00:25:42,120
Get down. Two fingers, then bam, bam.

345
00:25:43,560 --> 00:25:45,520
I need to film a video for my parents!

346
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:22,360
All good? You got it memorized, yeah?

347
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:23,880
I do. Okay.

348
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:27,360
Three, four, five, and six.

349
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:28,400
Seven, eight…

350
00:26:28,480 --> 00:26:29,400
Hey!

351
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:33,440
You okay?

352
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:36,040
Let's call it a day.

353
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:39,960
Why? I was just about to nail it.

354
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:44,200
Stop. Do as I say.

355
00:26:54,800 --> 00:26:57,160
KATE TEAW
ORIGINAL THAI BOAT NOODLE

356
00:27:04,440 --> 00:27:06,120
<i>How was practice?</i>

357
00:27:07,200 --> 00:27:09,800
DAD: GOOD MORNING

358
00:27:13,040 --> 00:27:15,200
<i>Your body not cooperating?</i>

359
00:27:16,400 --> 00:27:19,840
FUNAN: 272

360
00:27:54,480 --> 00:27:55,480
Aren't you gonna eat?

361
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:01,600
I…

362
00:28:02,320 --> 00:28:03,880
I'd like to apologize to you.

363
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,080
I…

364
00:28:09,560 --> 00:28:10,600
I did so poorly.

365
00:28:10,680 --> 00:28:14,320
I mean, I tried,
but it looked like I didn't, right?

366
00:28:15,040 --> 00:28:16,680
I'm not good at this.

367
00:28:18,600 --> 00:28:21,360
Take your time. You weren't born a dancer.

368
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:26,720
Maybe I'm not trying hard enough.

369
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,960
I could see that you were trying.

370
00:28:34,880 --> 00:28:36,040
Dig in already.

371
00:28:53,480 --> 00:28:54,880
You can have this too!

372
00:28:54,960 --> 00:28:56,680
Finish it. I'll order another one.

373
00:29:11,040 --> 00:29:13,240
Let me drive you home.

374
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:19,080
What's up with your tone?

375
00:29:21,800 --> 00:29:23,120
Someone here likes it.

376
00:29:26,760 --> 00:29:28,440
But he keeps his mouth shut.

377
00:29:37,880 --> 00:29:39,440
You think so?

378
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:46,120
Wanna pry it open?

379
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:07,680
So lame.

380
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:25,480
Jamie.

381
00:30:25,560 --> 00:30:26,960
Jamie, come here!

382
00:30:27,440 --> 00:30:28,640
Warrior, come this way.

383
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:30,160
Come here.

384
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:31,800
Here's your secret weapon.

385
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:32,760
A drink, please.

386
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:36,920
Wait. Your buddy, Duang,
isn't here with you?

387
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:39,160
No. He's on a lover-boy mission.

388
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:41,480
He's got someone?

389
00:30:41,560 --> 00:30:43,400
No, he's trying to win his crush's heart.

390
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:45,160
Okay.

391
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:46,320
And what about you?

392
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:48,520
What's the plan tonight?
Who's on your radar?

393
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:52,680
No one so far.

394
00:30:52,760 --> 00:30:54,640
Today, I'm going for an ambush.

395
00:30:54,720 --> 00:30:56,120
I'm diving in headfirst.

396
00:30:56,680 --> 00:30:59,440
All right! That's my bro.

397
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:06,200
"If you give someone a fish,
all they'll have is that fish.

398
00:31:06,760 --> 00:31:08,600
But if you teach someone how to fish,

399
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:10,480
they'll always have fish."

400
00:31:11,640 --> 00:31:12,520
You serious?

401
00:31:13,080 --> 00:31:14,720
This is who I am. Here, bottoms up.

402
00:31:24,960 --> 00:31:26,280
I was in the washroom.

403
00:31:34,720 --> 00:31:35,600
Go and get him.

404
00:31:36,600 --> 00:31:38,560
He never picks the same person twice,

405
00:31:39,120 --> 00:31:40,680
so you've got nothing to worry about.

406
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:43,720
If you can get him, that is.

407
00:32:09,680 --> 00:32:11,440
Shall we clink our glasses together?

408
00:32:26,560 --> 00:32:27,400
What's your name?

409
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:30,280
It's Mar.

410
00:32:30,960 --> 00:32:34,360
It's supposed to be "Mars." With an 'S'.

411
00:32:42,360 --> 00:32:45,640
Mars. It's the name of a planet.

412
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:55,560
And?

413
00:32:56,120 --> 00:32:58,440
My nickname, my real name,

414
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:00,200
or my stage name?

415
00:33:06,360 --> 00:33:07,560
What's your real name?

416
00:33:10,440 --> 00:33:11,280
Jettana.

417
00:33:36,800 --> 00:33:38,240
Let's take a photo.

418
00:33:38,320 --> 00:33:39,440
Hey, let me join you.

419
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:48,200
Yeah, that's the one.

420
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:49,120
Let me see.

421
00:33:50,160 --> 00:33:51,880
Go sit with your friends.

422
00:33:52,720 --> 00:33:53,800
- Hey, guys.
- Hello.

423
00:33:53,880 --> 00:33:54,960
Hello.

424
00:33:55,960 --> 00:33:59,080
I know you're on break, but we can't rest.

425
00:33:59,160 --> 00:34:01,040
That's why we're having
group practice today.

426
00:34:01,600 --> 00:34:03,520
What's the plan for today, Coach?

427
00:34:04,080 --> 00:34:05,400
Don't be so hasty now, okay?

428
00:34:05,480 --> 00:34:07,280
The tournament is soon, Coach.

429
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:08,360
We need to move.

430
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:11,040
Fine. This will be a practice
you'll never forget.

431
00:34:11,120 --> 00:34:13,719
We'll start by running five laps
around the court.

432
00:34:13,800 --> 00:34:14,960
Chop-chop!

433
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:15,920
- Come on!
- All right.

434
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:17,760
- Guys.
- Let's go.

435
00:34:23,120 --> 00:34:25,600
You'll be busy next semester.
Are you up for this, Qin?

436
00:34:26,280 --> 00:34:28,800
Yeah, you're usually not this busy.

437
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:30,440
Suddenly, you wanna be involved.

438
00:34:31,760 --> 00:34:34,440
I made my promise. I won't back out.

439
00:34:34,520 --> 00:34:37,679
Right. What about your lover boy?
Can he finally dance now?

440
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:41,440
He's got practice today. He'll manage.

441
00:34:42,120 --> 00:34:44,280
Hey! We've got slackers! Extra lap then!

442
00:34:45,159 --> 00:34:46,760
Shit! I wonder who the slackers are!

443
00:34:46,840 --> 00:34:48,440
You dare ask me that?

444
00:34:48,520 --> 00:34:49,480
Still there?

445
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:51,080
- Sorry.
- We're sorry.

446
00:34:51,159 --> 00:34:52,440
Go! Come on!

447
00:34:52,520 --> 00:34:53,920
After them.

448
00:35:20,600 --> 00:35:22,760
I think I'm getting better.
Don't you agree?

449
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:24,600
I wasn't watching.

450
00:35:26,240 --> 00:35:27,440
Ask him.

451
00:35:27,520 --> 00:35:28,440
Jamie.

452
00:35:29,640 --> 00:35:30,720
Don't ask me.

453
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:33,520
- You guys!
- Fine.

454
00:35:34,280 --> 00:35:36,160
Do it again. I'll watch this time.

455
00:35:37,160 --> 00:35:39,760
By the way,
you're actually serious about this.

456
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:41,960
I just thought it was for Qin.

457
00:35:42,520 --> 00:35:46,240
I just want to do my part.
I don't want to embarrass Qin.

458
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:48,600
Sheesh!

459
00:35:48,680 --> 00:35:50,520
You said that like you were his boyfriend.

460
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:52,600
Did I? I sounded like his boyfriend?

461
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:56,040
Duang, that doesn't mean
that you are, come on.

462
00:35:57,840 --> 00:35:59,600
That already confirms it.

463
00:36:00,120 --> 00:36:02,600
Do you really think Qin will say yes?

464
00:36:02,680 --> 00:36:04,880
Why wouldn't he want me? Hello!

465
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,760
Anyone who says no is missing out!

466
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:08,760
- I'm that cool.
- Who told you that?

467
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:11,360
I can say that to myself.

468
00:36:12,080 --> 00:36:15,200
Where is Qin, by the way?
Why did he leave you to practice alone?

469
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:17,120
Right.

470
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:18,600
He said he was busy.

471
00:36:18,680 --> 00:36:20,760
I forgot to ask him. Let me send him a DM.

472
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:22,120
No need.

473
00:36:32,840 --> 00:36:36,760
My dear Qin! I'll be there in a flash!

474
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:49,280
Duang isn't coming today?

475
00:36:49,360 --> 00:36:50,280
How would I know?

476
00:36:50,840 --> 00:36:51,960
We're not a thing.

477
00:36:52,040 --> 00:36:55,240
Currently, you're not.
What about in the future?

478
00:36:57,440 --> 00:36:58,360
No idea.

479
00:36:59,040 --> 00:37:00,360
Duang is a nice guy, you know?

480
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:03,120
He cares not only about you,
but also about us.

481
00:37:05,840 --> 00:37:07,600
People try hard to impress.

482
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:12,200
What?

483
00:37:13,440 --> 00:37:14,840
I like to take my time.

484
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:20,600
Taking too long can be bad.

485
00:37:20,680 --> 00:37:23,000
A fighter can become a quitter.

486
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:24,720
That's not my concern.

487
00:37:26,080 --> 00:37:30,040
If he wants to love-bomb me
and change when I say yes…

488
00:37:31,360 --> 00:37:32,760
what's the point then?

489
00:37:35,320 --> 00:37:37,480
I don't think
Duang is that type of person.

490
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:39,240
Yeah.

491
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:41,080
You're being judgmental.

492
00:37:41,600 --> 00:37:45,480
The problem isn't Duang.
You don't let anyone in.

493
00:37:45,560 --> 00:37:48,880
So much so, I feel bad for him.

494
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:50,520
This is who I am.

495
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:52,960
I'm not pushing anyone away.

496
00:37:53,640 --> 00:37:55,200
Right.

497
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:59,480
That means
you're opening up to the guy, correct?

498
00:38:16,760 --> 00:38:19,080
This lover boy what it takes, doesn't he?

499
00:38:19,720 --> 00:38:20,600
Yeah.

500
00:38:33,880 --> 00:38:34,760
Qin!

501
00:38:36,080 --> 00:38:37,400
Here, Tong, Kim.

502
00:38:40,040 --> 00:38:41,720
Are you tired? I bought you a drink.

503
00:38:44,840 --> 00:38:46,000
I'm not thirsty.

504
00:38:46,080 --> 00:38:48,320
Then I'll drink it. I'm tired now too.

505
00:38:59,040 --> 00:38:59,920
Right.

506
00:39:00,920 --> 00:39:02,920
I saw you on Tong's Story,
so I rushed over.

507
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:07,280
Duang!

508
00:39:08,640 --> 00:39:12,200
Duang, you should be a runner
if you're gonna be this fast.

509
00:39:12,760 --> 00:39:15,840
If you said your dad was The Flash,
I'd freaking believe you.

510
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:21,040
Qin!

511
00:39:22,600 --> 00:39:24,800
Qin!

512
00:39:24,880 --> 00:39:27,160
Tired from practice?

513
00:39:29,200 --> 00:39:30,240
Talking about yourself?

514
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:32,000
See that?

515
00:39:32,480 --> 00:39:33,880
Qin,

516
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:37,640
could there be a "we" with us now?

517
00:39:37,720 --> 00:39:39,600
I would wuv that.

518
00:39:42,200 --> 00:39:45,320
Qin, I awweady followed you.

519
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:47,680
Would you follow me back?

520
00:39:55,480 --> 00:39:56,320
You bastard!

521
00:39:56,400 --> 00:39:59,240
You jerk.
It took ages for him to follow me.

522
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:03,880
Why did you let him get so close to you?

523
00:40:03,960 --> 00:40:05,360
I'm sulky now.

524
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:12,240
Duang, what the hell?
You took so long to get to the point.

525
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:14,440
Let's go eat at Yang Noey.

526
00:40:14,520 --> 00:40:17,360
I'm hungry, and running didn't help.

527
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:20,360
Spit it out.

528
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:24,280
If you go, I go.

529
00:40:32,200 --> 00:40:33,120
What are you doing?

530
00:40:35,480 --> 00:40:37,080
Nope, nothing.

531
00:40:40,080 --> 00:40:43,120
HI, TONG. CAN YOU MEET ME
BEHIND THE UNIVERSITY?

532
00:40:43,200 --> 00:40:46,400
Damn, she hit me up again.

533
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:48,600
She wants to meet.

534
00:40:53,840 --> 00:40:56,360
My bad, Qin. Take care of him for me.

535
00:40:56,440 --> 00:40:57,600
- Peace out.
- What?

536
00:40:58,840 --> 00:40:59,920
Kim, let's go.

537
00:41:03,320 --> 00:41:04,520
Good luck.

538
00:41:16,520 --> 00:41:17,840
You know,

539
00:41:17,920 --> 00:41:20,240
the practice room
is so lonely without you.

540
00:41:20,320 --> 00:41:23,720
I really miss you.
Are you lonely without me?

541
00:41:25,280 --> 00:41:26,520
So, how was practice?

542
00:41:27,960 --> 00:41:29,800
Aren't you blushing a tiny bit?

543
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:34,040
I asked how was practice?

544
00:41:37,440 --> 00:41:39,320
- Let's pretend I didn't say that.
- What?

545
00:41:40,720 --> 00:41:43,160
I was just playing hard to get.

546
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:44,800
I'll show you.

547
00:41:46,480 --> 00:41:47,560
Give me a sec.

548
00:41:47,640 --> 00:41:48,760
Hold on.

549
00:41:50,760 --> 00:41:52,160
- Let's go.
- Ready?

550
00:41:52,720 --> 00:41:53,800
- Ready.
- Go.

551
00:41:53,880 --> 00:41:56,800
One, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

552
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:57,840
Enough.

553
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:03,480
All right, I believe you.

554
00:42:05,640 --> 00:42:07,120
I worked so hard at practice.

555
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:08,920
Just ask Pae and Jamie.

556
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:10,080
It's true.

557
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:11,680
He really did work hard.

558
00:42:11,760 --> 00:42:14,640
I swear on the Tiger Adventure.

559
00:42:16,720 --> 00:42:17,560
My bad, bro.

560
00:42:19,400 --> 00:42:22,360
It's true, though.
You should be proud of him.

561
00:42:30,480 --> 00:42:31,840
Give me your keys then.

562
00:42:34,200 --> 00:42:35,320
I'll drive.

563
00:42:38,600 --> 00:42:41,840
No way. You're tired from practice.
I'll drive.

564
00:42:48,240 --> 00:42:49,760
Are we going or what?

565
00:42:51,520 --> 00:42:52,840
Duang is the bottom.

566
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:58,960
Seriously, both of you are handsome.

567
00:42:59,680 --> 00:43:01,800
But the shipper told me that

568
00:43:01,880 --> 00:43:05,000
a sweet face like this is the bottom.

569
00:43:07,720 --> 00:43:08,720
I think Qin is cuter.

570
00:43:10,800 --> 00:43:12,040
That doesn't matter, does it?

571
00:43:12,120 --> 00:43:13,840
You are really cute, though.

572
00:43:14,560 --> 00:43:15,920
Whatever. Suit yourself.

573
00:43:18,640 --> 00:43:21,160
The way you're talking,
are you interested in me now?

574
00:43:24,560 --> 00:43:25,840
Give me the keys.

575
00:43:51,760 --> 00:43:53,240
Qin's so freaking adorable.

576
00:43:53,800 --> 00:43:55,680
See? Duang is the bottom.

577
00:43:56,480 --> 00:43:57,320
Pae, seriously?

578
00:43:57,400 --> 00:43:59,120
- How much?
- It's 200 baht.

579
00:43:59,200 --> 00:44:00,560
Then you're the top.

580
00:44:01,560 --> 00:44:03,520
Qin! Wait for me.

581
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:08,960
YANG NOEY

582
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:17,200
Oops!

583
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:20,240
Oopsie.

584
00:44:20,320 --> 00:44:21,880
- Pae.
- That's enough.

585
00:44:22,440 --> 00:44:23,440
Save some for yourself.

586
00:44:39,040 --> 00:44:40,080
They're having a moment.

587
00:44:40,880 --> 00:44:43,040
Duang, don't die on us.
Your smile needs a doctor.

588
00:44:49,720 --> 00:44:51,000
There's no pork left.

589
00:44:53,480 --> 00:44:54,840
You…

590
00:44:54,920 --> 00:44:55,840
What?

591
00:44:57,040 --> 00:44:59,680
You're just so cute. I can't take it.

592
00:45:05,520 --> 00:45:06,520
Jamie.

593
00:45:11,400 --> 00:45:13,400
I can't take it either.

594
00:45:13,480 --> 00:45:15,480
Gimme all the pork you want.

595
00:45:18,480 --> 00:45:19,880
Thank you.

596
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:22,840
Thank you.

597
00:45:23,920 --> 00:45:26,440
Hey, why are you doing that for them?

598
00:45:28,480 --> 00:45:30,320
Ugh.

599
00:45:30,400 --> 00:45:32,120
Can't you use chopsticks?

600
00:45:32,720 --> 00:45:33,680
Qin!

601
00:45:34,440 --> 00:45:35,480
My best bro.

602
00:45:41,720 --> 00:45:42,600
What a small world.

603
00:45:43,240 --> 00:45:44,720
Yeah, hey.

604
00:45:46,920 --> 00:45:49,000
Can I sit with you guys?

605
00:45:53,120 --> 00:45:55,600
And you're here all by yourself?

606
00:45:55,680 --> 00:45:58,440
I got the date wrong.

607
00:45:59,600 --> 00:46:01,600
Come sit with us.
Qin's friend is also mine.

608
00:46:01,680 --> 00:46:02,760
Facts.

609
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:04,840
Can I have this stool?

610
00:46:06,560 --> 00:46:08,000
I'm not holding back then.

611
00:46:08,480 --> 00:46:13,360
Waiter, one plate, one spoon,
and one pair of chopsticks, please.

612
00:46:14,960 --> 00:46:17,320
- Where are you going?
- To get dessert.

613
00:46:17,400 --> 00:46:18,440
I'll come with you.

614
00:46:28,760 --> 00:46:29,640
Sup, bro?

615
00:46:31,800 --> 00:46:33,160
Sup, bro?

616
00:46:37,560 --> 00:46:39,280
Cho, are you Qin's school friend?

617
00:46:39,360 --> 00:46:41,560
Yeah, we were in marching band together.

618
00:46:41,640 --> 00:46:43,600
So how was Qin back then?

619
00:46:46,400 --> 00:46:47,280
Studious,

620
00:46:47,360 --> 00:46:49,320
good-looking, athletic,

621
00:46:49,400 --> 00:46:51,120
and the teachers' pet.

622
00:46:53,400 --> 00:46:55,600
- How flawless of you, Qin.
- Yeah.

623
00:46:56,120 --> 00:46:57,840
So were you a hot guy?

624
00:46:58,800 --> 00:47:00,760
That's enough. I'm sitting right here.

625
00:47:01,240 --> 00:47:02,600
He was so freaking hot.

626
00:47:02,680 --> 00:47:04,280
But he didn't care about anyone,

627
00:47:04,840 --> 00:47:08,120
except my friend, Tiw.

628
00:47:13,640 --> 00:47:15,080
Just let me talk about him.

629
00:47:15,160 --> 00:47:18,600
It was a long time ago.
And you two already broke up.

630
00:47:19,640 --> 00:47:21,040
We didn't break up or anything.

631
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:23,280
Fine, you didn't.

632
00:47:23,800 --> 00:47:24,960
But here's something spicy.

633
00:47:25,040 --> 00:47:26,720
No way!

634
00:47:27,680 --> 00:47:30,120
Tiw, my friend, gave Qin a teddy bear

635
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:32,680
in front of everyone at school.

636
00:47:33,360 --> 00:47:36,040
He wanted everyone to know Qin was his.

637
00:47:41,640 --> 00:47:44,400
Right. It's all in the past.

638
00:47:44,480 --> 00:47:46,160
Let's talk about something else.

639
00:47:46,240 --> 00:47:47,360
That's right!

640
00:47:49,160 --> 00:47:50,120
But…

641
00:47:53,160 --> 00:47:56,200
If you want to get back with him,
just tell me.

642
00:47:57,160 --> 00:47:58,480
Shut up and finish your food.

643
00:48:00,960 --> 00:48:03,040
You're still as harsh as ever, I see.

644
00:48:04,040 --> 00:48:05,400
Duang needs your help.

645
00:48:08,000 --> 00:48:09,560
Qin, is the grass jelly good?

646
00:48:11,280 --> 00:48:12,120
It's decent.

647
00:48:13,280 --> 00:48:14,200
Do you want more?

648
00:48:15,760 --> 00:48:17,480
- Let--
- What do you think of Duang?

649
00:48:19,720 --> 00:48:20,920
Shit.

650
00:48:23,280 --> 00:48:24,520
Duang and Qin are…

651
00:48:24,600 --> 00:48:26,600
It's what you're thinking.

652
00:48:27,600 --> 00:48:28,440
Ding, ding.

653
00:48:31,200 --> 00:48:33,560
Damn. I'm so sorry.

654
00:48:34,120 --> 00:48:36,440
It's okay! It's fine.

655
00:48:37,240 --> 00:48:38,280
Right.

656
00:48:38,840 --> 00:48:41,680
So, Qin, what do you think of Duang?

657
00:48:53,360 --> 00:48:55,120
I'll get you another bowl.

658
00:49:01,600 --> 00:49:03,200
Duang is too naive, Qin.

659
00:49:03,280 --> 00:49:04,960
You've got to spell it out for him.

660
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:08,560
- He's extremely clueless.
- Yeah.

661
00:49:08,640 --> 00:49:09,960
Isn't that right?

662
00:49:11,800 --> 00:49:12,720
Clueless.

663
00:49:14,280 --> 00:49:15,920
Hey, I think I should leave.

664
00:49:16,000 --> 00:49:17,960
I'll pay you later. Just tell me how much.

665
00:49:18,760 --> 00:49:20,160
Wait.

666
00:49:23,720 --> 00:49:26,960
Pay up right now. It's 319 baht.

667
00:49:28,160 --> 00:49:29,760
It's 319 baht…

668
00:49:32,240 --> 00:49:33,160
There!

669
00:49:33,240 --> 00:49:34,440
Hey, wait!

670
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:37,960
What are you doing? Follow him!

671
00:49:38,600 --> 00:49:41,440
- There goes your 319 baht.
- It's fine. We'll split it.

672
00:50:01,240 --> 00:50:03,400
Guys. I've got to go now.

673
00:50:03,480 --> 00:50:04,960
I gotta talk to my crush.

674
00:50:07,000 --> 00:50:10,040
Qin, I'm completely hammered.

675
00:50:11,760 --> 00:50:12,640
We didn't drink.

676
00:50:12,720 --> 00:50:14,360
You're so pretentious.

677
00:50:14,440 --> 00:50:15,720
What a cheeky little guy.

678
00:50:17,520 --> 00:50:18,840
You caught me.

679
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:21,920
Would it kill you to be nice to me?

680
00:50:23,040 --> 00:50:24,320
Qin smiled!

681
00:50:27,960 --> 00:50:29,840
You lied to me again. You're a bad friend.

682
00:50:31,080 --> 00:50:32,920
Stop fighting. I have to go as well.

683
00:50:36,240 --> 00:50:37,120
I'll take you home.

684
00:50:39,320 --> 00:50:40,240
I called a ride.

685
00:50:42,880 --> 00:50:45,160
Qin already called his ride,
but I haven't.

686
00:50:45,240 --> 00:50:46,200
Take me home instead.

687
00:50:47,640 --> 00:50:48,520
Are you Qin?

688
00:50:49,360 --> 00:50:51,000
- Then no.
- What?

689
00:50:51,640 --> 00:50:52,800
Well then…

690
00:50:53,720 --> 00:50:56,600
Qin, let me use your name for a bit.

691
00:51:00,480 --> 00:51:02,160
Duang, call me Qin.

692
00:51:03,040 --> 00:51:03,880
I'm going.

693
00:51:06,080 --> 00:51:07,080
Bye-bye.

694
00:51:11,160 --> 00:51:12,360
I should go home as well.

695
00:51:15,560 --> 00:51:16,960
My name is Qin.

696
00:51:17,040 --> 00:51:19,240
- So take me home.
- Hell no.

697
00:51:20,200 --> 00:51:22,560
What do you mean? I'm Qin now.

698
00:51:23,280 --> 00:51:25,720
- You're so pretentious. Just go home!
- We're friends.

699
00:51:25,800 --> 00:51:28,360
We're on a break. Tit for tat.

700
00:51:28,440 --> 00:51:29,920
Fair's fair.

701
00:51:33,200 --> 00:51:34,040
Duang!

702
00:51:47,280 --> 00:51:49,000
Why are you following me?

703
00:51:49,800 --> 00:51:51,400
It's none of your business.

704
00:51:51,480 --> 00:51:52,400
Fine, damn it.

705
00:51:52,480 --> 00:51:53,840
Just get outta here.

706
00:51:55,040 --> 00:51:56,800
Don't try to act tough with me, Duang.

707
00:51:58,760 --> 00:52:01,800
A stranger
addressing someone inappropriately…

708
00:52:01,880 --> 00:52:03,120
How ill-mannered.

709
00:52:09,760 --> 00:52:12,560
If I were not this well-behaved…

710
00:52:13,440 --> 00:52:15,360
What would you have done?

711
00:52:16,080 --> 00:52:17,160
Look what you did to me!

712
00:52:17,240 --> 00:52:20,040
I'd soak my shoes in water

713
00:52:20,120 --> 00:52:22,000
and kick the shit out of you.

714
00:52:22,080 --> 00:52:24,080
- Get ready for it.
- Go away!

715
00:52:29,240 --> 00:52:31,280
What did I do to upset you?

716
00:52:32,960 --> 00:52:35,320
You leaned on Qin's shoulder.

717
00:52:35,400 --> 00:52:37,640
And you talked to him too much!

718
00:52:38,520 --> 00:52:40,600
You're hitting on him
when you know I like him!

719
00:52:43,280 --> 00:52:45,400
Gosh. This is hilarious.

720
00:52:45,960 --> 00:52:47,640
Why are you this upset?

721
00:52:49,200 --> 00:52:50,920
Stop laughing, damn it.

722
00:52:54,000 --> 00:52:56,040
Instead of being mad at me,

723
00:52:56,120 --> 00:52:59,080
you should think about Qin's teddy.

724
00:52:59,160 --> 00:53:00,400
Right?

725
00:53:02,920 --> 00:53:04,280
Yeah, you're right.

726
00:53:05,160 --> 00:53:06,680
I don't know what to do next.

727
00:53:07,840 --> 00:53:09,520
He still has that teddy.

728
00:53:11,240 --> 00:53:14,240
So you're taking it out on me?

729
00:53:19,080 --> 00:53:20,480
Qin…

730
00:53:22,760 --> 00:53:24,720
What the hell are you saying?

731
00:53:24,800 --> 00:53:26,840
Stop crying like a wet puppy.

732
00:53:26,920 --> 00:53:28,280
Hush!

733
00:53:28,360 --> 00:53:29,440
Quiet now.

734
00:53:40,680 --> 00:53:43,320
At first, I didn't think
his walls were that high.

735
00:53:44,240 --> 00:53:47,560
I thought I could get over them.
I guess I was delusional.

736
00:53:49,600 --> 00:53:53,280
But you're the first
to stand up to his walls.

737
00:54:00,880 --> 00:54:03,240
Does keeping that teddy
really mean nothing at all?

738
00:54:05,040 --> 00:54:08,120
So you're giving up?

739
00:54:13,920 --> 00:54:15,680
I'm worried about Qin.

740
00:54:16,640 --> 00:54:18,360
I'm worried he'd choose that person.

741
00:54:19,440 --> 00:54:22,120
I'm worried he'll just flat out reject me.

742
00:54:23,920 --> 00:54:25,960
I don't know what I'm supposed to do now.

743
00:54:31,320 --> 00:54:33,280
I told you not to get your hopes up.

744
00:54:35,400 --> 00:54:37,560
I really didn't see this coming.

745
00:54:38,480 --> 00:54:41,840
Let me ask you something.
In the next two years,

746
00:54:42,320 --> 00:54:45,880
will you treat him the same way you did
at the BBQ place?

747
00:54:47,200 --> 00:54:49,080
What does that have to do
with what I said?

748
00:54:49,160 --> 00:54:51,280
- Were you listening to me?
- Come on.

749
00:54:52,280 --> 00:54:53,160
Answer me.

750
00:55:01,520 --> 00:55:05,360
I've devoted my love to him,
and I'll never give up.

751
00:55:06,360 --> 00:55:07,880
All I care about is

752
00:55:07,960 --> 00:55:10,320
whether he likes something
or wants something…

753
00:55:11,720 --> 00:55:14,480
If he wants me to
grill some pork for him, I'll do it.

754
00:55:15,320 --> 00:55:16,920
If he wants me to peel shrimp, I will.

755
00:55:21,040 --> 00:55:22,760
If he no longer wants it…

756
00:55:25,600 --> 00:55:26,600
I'll stop.

757
00:55:27,600 --> 00:55:28,720
That's how I see it.

758
00:55:35,240 --> 00:55:36,760
Warrior, I hate you.

759
00:55:37,800 --> 00:55:39,000
Trying to be emotional.

760
00:55:40,800 --> 00:55:42,040
That's it.

761
00:55:42,120 --> 00:55:43,520
Keep it going.

762
00:55:43,600 --> 00:55:47,000
If something bothers you,
just vent with me.

763
00:55:54,480 --> 00:55:56,760
Shit. Something big is coming.

764
00:55:57,560 --> 00:55:58,400
What?

765
00:55:58,480 --> 00:56:00,920
Seven-one-five-three.
Seven-one-five-three.

766
00:56:01,720 --> 00:56:04,240
Seven-one-five-three.

767
00:56:04,320 --> 00:56:05,560
What are you saying?

768
00:56:05,640 --> 00:56:07,080
Hey, my ride is here.

769
00:56:07,160 --> 00:56:09,080
What? Aren't I driving you?

770
00:56:09,160 --> 00:56:10,520
Bye! Be seeing you!

771
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:11,720
Call me if you need me!

772
00:56:11,800 --> 00:56:13,360
- Don't overthink it.
- What?

773
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:19,400
Jamie! You idiot.

774
00:58:54,920 --> 00:58:57,480
This is Yim,
your modeling partner for the shoot.

775
00:58:57,560 --> 00:59:00,320
All you've been doing
is playing hard to get. And see?

776
00:59:00,400 --> 00:59:01,880
He seemed jealous of Yim and me.

777
00:59:01,960 --> 00:59:03,160
You just realized it?

778
00:59:03,240 --> 00:59:04,400
Were you jealous?

779
00:59:05,840 --> 00:59:07,840
You're here to shop, right?
Or to meet someone?

780
00:59:07,920 --> 00:59:09,920
I'm not meeting anyone. You are.

781
00:59:11,160 --> 00:59:14,080
My parents told me, "If you love someone,

782
00:59:14,160 --> 00:59:16,160
try spending the night
in their room first."
